metadata.title: Inspecting an Event
metadata.content:
Inspecting an Event
The Event details will provide all the information to understand how this event was received, which data it contained and the tools to reproduce it locally.

metadata.title: Inspecting an Event
metadata.content:
Inspecting an Event
Accessing Events
Events across all application of the currently
[selected environment](\docs\platform\environments)
are accessible via the "Events" page in the left side navigation.
The Events list features the last events received.
*Events can be filtered using a time filter.*
Accessing the events of a specific Event Type is achieved via the "Event Types" menu.

metadata.title: Inspecting an Event
metadata.content:
Inspecting an Event
Searching Events
Advanced filters are available using a
[CEL expression](\docs\guides\writing-expressions)
. The search feature is available by clicking on the "Show search" button.
The events list features an advance search feature that filters results using a CEL query.

metadata.title: Inspecting an Event
metadata.content:
Inspecting an Event
Searching Events
Searchable properties
Only basic search operators and the
```
event
```
variable are available for now:
```
== != == != == != > >= < <= == != == != > >= < <=
```
event.id, Type = string. event.id, Operators = 
A few examples of valid search queries are
```
event.data.hello == "world"
```
and
```
event.name != "billing"
```
.
[Learn more about how expressions are used in Inngest.](\docs\guides\writing-expressions)
You can combine multiple search queries using the
```
&&
```
operator or
```
||
```
operator. Adding a new line is the equivalent of using the
```
&&
```
operator.
